## 4. Refactoring `buildTreeWithChanges` (for `WriteTemporary`)

### Current Flow
```
buildTreeWithChanges
  -> FlattenTree(baseTree)           // O(N) where N = all files in repo
  -> modify entries (add/delete)     // O(changed files)
  -> BuildTreeFromEntries(entries)   // O(N) rebuild entire tree
```

### New Flow
```
buildTreeWithChanges
  -> collect changes as []TreeChange
  -> ApplyTreeChanges(baseTreeHash, changes)  // O(depth * changed_dirs)
```

### Detailed Changes

The `ApplyTreeChanges` function groups changes by their first path segment and recurses:

```go
func ApplyTreeChanges(repo *git.Repository, rootTreeHash plumbing.Hash, changes []TreeChange) (plumbing.Hash, error) {
    if len(changes) == 0 {
        return rootTreeHash, nil
    }

    // Read the current root tree
    var currentEntries []object.TreeEntry
    if rootTreeHash != plumbing.ZeroHash {
        tree, err := repo.TreeObject(rootTreeHash)
        if err != nil {
            return plumbing.ZeroHash, err
        }
        currentEntries = make([]object.TreeEntry, len(tree.Entries))
        copy(currentEntries, tree.Entries)
    }

    // Group changes by first path segment
    type dirChanges struct {
        subChanges []TreeChange // Changes within this subdirectory (paths stripped of first segment)
        fileChange *TreeChange  // Direct file change at this level (nil if directory)
    }
    grouped := make(map[string]*dirChanges)

    for i := range changes {
        c := changes[i]
        parts := strings.SplitN(c.Path, "/", 2)
        name := parts[0]
        if grouped[name] == nil {
            grouped[name] = &dirChanges{}
        }
        if len(parts) == 1 {
            // File at this level
            cc := c
            grouped[name].fileChange = &cc
        } else {
            // In a subdirectory
            grouped[name].subChanges = append(grouped[name].subChanges, TreeChange{
                Path:  parts[1],
                Entry: c.Entry,
            })

## 2. Core New Function: `UpdateSubtree`

### Location: `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/tree_surgery.go` (new file)

This function performs "tree surgery" -- it modifies a subtree at a given path within an existing tree without flattening. The key insight is that you can reuse all unchanged subtree hashes.

### Function Signature

```go
// UpdateSubtree replaces or creates a subtree at the given path within an existing tree.
// It walks the tree path, replacing only the entries along the modified path.
// All sibling entries at each level retain their original hashes (no re-reading or re-building).
//
// pathSegments is the directory path split into segments (e.g., ["a3", "b2c4d5e6f7", "0"]).
// newEntries are the files to place at the leaf directory (replaces that directory's contents).
// If existingEntries is non-nil, they are merged with newEntries (existing entries not in newEntries are kept).
//
// Returns the new root tree hash.
func UpdateSubtree(
    repo *git.Repository,
    rootTreeHash plumbing.Hash,
    pathSegments []string,
    newEntries []object.TreeEntry,
    opts UpdateSubtreeOptions,
) (plumbing.Hash, error)

// UpdateSubtreeOptions configures the behavior of UpdateSubtree.
type UpdateSubtreeOptions struct {
    // MergeMode controls how entries at the leaf directory are handled.
    // ReplaceAll replaces the entire directory contents.
    // MergeKeepExisting keeps existing entries not overwritten by newEntries.
    MergeMode MergeMode

    // DeletePaths lists paths (relative to the leaf directory) to delete.
    // Only applicable when MergeMode is MergeKeepExisting.
    DeletePaths []string
}

type MergeMode int

const (
    // ReplaceAll replaces the entire leaf directory contents with newEntries.
    ReplaceAll MergeMode = iota
    // MergeKeepExisting merges newEntries into the existing leaf directory,
    // keeping entries not overwritten by newEntries (unless in DeletePaths).
    MergeKeepExisting
)
